	1 what is GIT and GIThup?
	2 How to install GIT software
	3 Hwo to commit code to GIT repository
	4 How ot puch code to GITHub repository?
	5 How to integrate  GitHup & Jenkins
	
	GIT and GITHUB hum source code maintain karne k liye use karte hai.GIT or GIThub dono alag alag cheeze hai.
	GIt ko hum system me istall karte hai or GIThub hamara remote repository hota hai.
	Jab bhi tester ya developer code lkhta hai to uska source code  initially working directory/workspace me hota hai.
	uske baad aata hai Staging area. workspace se code hum direct GIT repository me bhej nahi sakta. uske pehle hume code staging area me add karna hota hai.
	uske baad aata hai GIt repository jo hamare local machine me istall hota hai.  uske baad aaata hai GITHUB repository jo ki remote
	repository hota hai.
	
#########################	workflow   #################################33

1. Workspace/working directory > (Adding code) stageing area > (Commit code) GIT Repository > (push code) GITHUB repository
 
2. Workspace/working diectory pull code directly from GIThub Repository.

for adding code to staging area:- git add command
for committing code to git local repository:- git commit command
for sending code to github repository from git repository:- git push
for taking code from github repository:- git pull


